SIMPLE: under-arm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Under-arm
<hw>Un"der-arm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Cricket)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Done (as bowling) with the arm not raised above the
elbow, that is, not swung far out from the body; underhand. Cf.
<er>Over-arm</er> and <er>Round-Arm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>For use under the arms, specifically in the armpit;
<as>as, an <ex>underarm</ex> deodorant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underback</ent>⟦br⟧
